title: Nice, but not my style
text: I bought 7 necklaces from this seller. How can you not when they are so cheap?  While it did make nervous that the pieces were so cheap, I figured that unless they arrived completely destroyed, I would be able to fix any of them up or add a new chain if need be.  All pieces arrived intact. I tweaked a few rough edges and closed a few jump rings, but nothing crazy. This piece is definitely not my style and I knew it was a risk when I ordered it.  Still gave it a high rating however, as there is nothing wrong with the actual piece. I may try to tweak it and make it more like something I would wear.  I am going to order more items from this seller.

title: Great comfort and many colors
text: I originally purchased these socks in all black in two sizes in packs of three. Both felt great but had to turn down the top of large socks because they came over knee. Very comfortable and good tapered compression. I’ve been wearing these type of socks for varicose veins for years. These socks are the best I’ve ever used. I decided to order additional socks that are available in different colors and patterns. These were packaged as single pairs. I ordered eight pair of different colors and patterns in the smaller size. Couldn’t have been more pleased. The packaging was very up scale and reminded me of packaging by apple. It set the tone for what was inside… a very high quality sock. All socks even the all black that I ordered originally in three pack have withstood many machine washings on cold cycle. I hang them up for quick dry. I also like the logo at the top and colored heels and toes. This feature allow me to align socks on sock donner for quick and accurate alignment. I really like adding color back into my wardrobe. I think over the years there haven’t been many choice for those of us that are limited  to compression socks. Thanks for providing a great product! I tried another brand that had interesting colors but inside of sock was not finished well and was lacking improper support. This is a combined report for three multiple purchases over last three or four months. Thanks for delivering a quality product that looks and feels good and gives support.

title: Good for the price
text: This is a nice set of bangles. They are the sort you might find at a Claires. They are not high quality but they are a little over $5. This is a nice price point for these bangles. Great set, on the cheaper side.

title: Lovely necklace
text:
This is a very pretty layered necklace. Layer one has a small heart and layer two has a bigger heart with a heart shaped hole. The necklace is gold plated and cubic zirconia. This is a great gift and comes in a very nice box and pouch.

It is a very delicate chain. It is fragile but if you take care of it, it will last. I have not had any broken chains with these necklaces and I have had a few this delicate and thin.

title: What a great way to surprise someone that they are going to be an aunt!
text:
I really like these bracelets. The black string bracelet is very thin. There is a bead that secures pushes up securing the bracelet. It is not a good mechanism as it comes loose pretty often. I have found the bracelet on the floor after taking off my jacket. It gets caught in my jacket easily and the clasp is not strong enough to secure it. So, be careful and mindful.

I love the fact that the message is in Morse code and therefore not a whole lot of people will know what it says. It makes for a great gift. The beads are gold plated in 14k gold.

The bracelet comes in a ready to gift box.

I think any aunt would love this (I do), especially a new one. I imagine this would be a great reveal gift for a new aunt. Telling her it is Morse code and she needs to figure out what it says.

title: These are great!
text: These are awesome. They are great when walking around the house to prevent slips and falls. They are super comfortable and the bag goes up a bit over the back of your ankle. I find that a problem with ankle socks is that they do not cover the back and you gt blister. That is not the case here.

title: Cool,dry,stylish
text: Really nice shirt. Very casual and comfortable. I got this for my dad to try who most of the time,depending on the brand wears a size medium or a large. This particular shirt is in Asian sizes so fortunately we ordered a large/Asian L. The material is ventilated and stays dry. The shirt stays pretty dry despite sweating. We both love the style. It washes well no shrinking. He and I both recommend giving this shirt a dry. Very stylish. Keep the Asian sizing in mind when ordering.

title: Gorgeous crystals
text: These are very pretty colorful earrings. Perfect for work, dressing for dinner and dressy casual. The crystals hit the light just right. These match almost everything in my closet. They're comfortable. They're lightweight enough to wear all day comfortably. These are very giftable, comes in a nice box so it can be sent directly to the recipient.

title: Simple classy
text: These are cute dainty necklaces. Made to be worn together.  One gold bar and one beveled gold circle. Adjustable length. You can also wear each of them alone. The same brand also sells each design alone

title: Great quality, very warm
text: Got this for my Dad to try. He LOVES IT! It's warm and covers his ears perfectly keeping his head and ears warm. The material is comfortable. It protects your head and ears from bone chilling wind. Great quality at a great price. Can't recommend enough!

title: Comfortable and colorful
text: These adorable, colorful socks fit well and are quite comfortable.  I use then to take walks. Plus I also wear them around the house. My feet don't sweat in them. They wash well and don't shrink. I love the style, they're colorful unique.

title: It's an ok necklace
text: I usually go for silver accessories over "fake" gold, but I actually think this is a cute little necklace. The chain is thin and not "sturdy". I also don't see the gold color holding up too long and will tarnish. It is cute and I'll probably wear it sometimes as long as it holds up. I think it'd be very cute for a young girl teenager. I have to say though that the price is a bit high for the quality.

title: Junk!
text: I personally found this necklace to be very cheap and for lack of a better word cheesey looking. This necklace came up on my Vine queue. I like what's supposed to be .925 silver. I decided to try it out. It reminds me if those $1 necklaces you get on that one app where they claim to be silver and come from China. It's very cute and would be nice for a very young girl 10-12 years old. If it costs more than $2 it's too much. Also the clasp would get stuck open. It comes in a little zip lock bag. I really don't recommend this necklace.

title: Great Gift!
text: My husband really likes bracelets - well, bracelets and watches. So, I am always on the lookout for interesting new bracelets for him to enjoy. Because he's a little rough on stuff, bracelets don't last too long. He actually had a similar style leather bracelet that we got about six months ago, and we had to superglue it back together - so I am hoping the metal clasp on this one is sturdier. The three bands means that it is more breathable on his skin and as warmer weather approaches, I think that this will be a favorite. The brown leather is nicely braided and he was pretty enthusiastic about it when he opened it. It makes a great gift, and has a nice velvety bag with a drawstring enclosure that is included. My husband has a larger wrist size, and this fits him snugly, but not too snugly, so I would say that it definitely runs to the larger side.

title: Very Pretty
text: I love this shape of earring that are a little like ear crawlers, so you can twist them so that the swoops of the leaves goes up your ear, rather than hangs down it. The rose gold color is really pretty. These are a little larger than I first expected, so they come a bit closer to being on the gaudy side. But, they catch the light nicely and have a very "spring" look to them. I can see that these would be a great gift for Mother's Day!

title: Perfect To Bring A Little Sunshine To Your Outfit!
text: I really like this flowing little open tunic top - it's versatile and so very bright and cheerful! I think it's probably too casual to wear to work, but I definitely would recommend it for weekend wear! I think that you can pair this with a variety of outfits underneath and really make it feel like something new, even though it really does stand out because of the lovely sunshine color. I think that a more neutral color might be even more versatile, but just wouldn't be as fun! This is a definite addition to my next vacation bag!!

title: Cute For Layering!
text: I don't usually like sweaters that are so "holey" but I like this oatmeal color a lot - plus, you can wear it for a longer range of months because it requires layering. With a tank underneath, it's fine for summer! With longer sleeves underneath, perfect for fall! And with a tank under and then a larger cardigan over, it works for fall/winter! I am a little scared of something snagging it, but other than that, it's a great and versatile sweater!

title: Very Comfortable, Just the Right Amount of Compression
text: Here's what my wife had to say about these socks: I have been a fan of Forcool socks since I bought my first pair, and these socks are no exception. They have extra padding and cushion in the toes, the balls of the feet, the top of the foot, and the Achilles tendon area, all areas that have a potential to rub or chaff when out walking, running, or hiking. They provide a comfortable amount of compression which keeps them from slipping or bunching up, and yet provide excellent flexibility no matter how I move or twist my feet. Each sock has a pull tab in the back that is useful for getting the sock on. There is extra ribbing on the sole of each sock for added arch support. The seams are totally smooth and well sewn. There are breathable mesh "windows" on the sides of each sock to allow for ventilation. As an added plus, the socks are stylish in their pattern and design. A mesh laundry bag is included. An insert explains that using the mesh bag will help extend the life of my socks. These are excellent socks, and I'm very pleased with them.

title: Work Well for Cleaning
text: Per my wife: These long yellow gloves fit nicely in a size small and go all the way up to within three inches of my elbow. They are more than long enough for me to immerse my hands in soapy water or to scrub out showers and other areas without getting my hands and forearms covered with chemical cleaning agents. The gloves have raised grips, like a screen door pattern, in all the fingertips and on the palms. This helps give me a better grip on things like scrub brushes or cleaning cloths. the gloves have a cheerful flower pattern on the back of each hand. The gloves are thick enough to make me think they will hold up under regular use, and yet they are flexible enough that I can easily bend my fingers and twist my hands around as needed when cleaning things. The extra ribbing around the top of the gloves created a good seal to keep the gloves from slipping off and to keep water from entering the gloves. 5 stars.

title: Good Work Belts, Good Price
text: These are extremely strong work type belts.  Having worn actual "tactical" belts I wouldn't actually call these "tactical" unless you're talking about paintball.  I've been using these type belts for the past year or so and none have worn out yet.  I suspect they'll outlive me.  Important to note that you do have to remove one of the buckles to fit the belt through standard belt loops.  Bottom line is that the quick release feature works great if you're not changing the belt but every time you put the belt on a new pair of pants, you have to remove one of the buckles - and you can only remove one of the two - in order to string it through a normal set of belt loops.  Basically you leave the two parts of the "buckle" connected, sting the belt through your belt loops and then restring the webbing  through the one side of the buckle.  It's quick and easy once you get used to it.  They recommend that you not cut the belt but I cut it a 3 or 4 inches longer than I need and sear the new end with a heat gun.  Works great.  A number of 3 belts sets on Amazon are identical, and I mean identical, but these are the least expensive I've found.

title: Comfortable and Good Looking
text: Socks fit as expected.  Appropriate for casual wear. All around I liked these socks with one small exception.  Where the pattern changes in color there is some excess material on the inside of the socks.  Most of it doesn't bother me but the excess material near the toes tended to get my attention in a negative way.  I suspect I just have extra sensitive toes.  The material didn't bother me anywhere else.

title: Super Cute!
text:
Being that I love earrings and silver, when I saw these up for request on Vine I clicked right away and here we are! This review is for: S925 Sterling Silver Handsome Cool Personality Circle Trendy Earrings with S925 Silver Needle for Women Girls.

In short, these are super cute. It's the little charms on there that make these special. The charms almost look like the tool icon on my PC. The only problem with them is that they can easily fall off when taking the earrings on and off. The charms are so small that if they fall off you might have a difficult time finding them again! It is the charms though that move about a little bit and catch the eye.

These are sterling silver and they caused no irritation to my ears like cheap earrings often do. For the price these earrings are a good buy and because they're silver they should last a good long time. Just be careful of those tiny charms!

title: Cool Rings!
text:
Being that I started reviewing here at Amazon by reviewing horror books, these rings are right up my alley! That is why I requested them from Vine. This review is for: YADOCA 9 Pieces Vintage Punk Rings Octopus Dragon Snake Adjustable Ring for Men Women Silver Black Claw

To be honest, I really was after the tentacle ring. For anyone into the Cthulhu mythos, tentacles play a part in that and when I saw that ring I had to request this set.

The rest of the rings are okay. Some of them have too high of a profile for me to wear. By that, I mean they stick out a lot at the top. I have problems with them catching in drawers and catching on anything, in fact.

I like the snake rings as well. The skulls and stuff really aren't for me, but I know someone at work that would like them. I did find that not all of the rings are adjustable, so just be aware of that fact.

By the price I'm sure you can tell this isn't expensive or bougie jewelry. However, for the price this set of 9 rings is a good buy. So far, I haven't had any problems with the ones I've worn. If that changes, I will come back and adjust my review accordingly. As of right now, these rings are just what I expected! Long live Cthulhu!

title: Okay
text:
This review is of: Udalyn 4 Pendant Necklace Tassel Necklace Electroplating Platinum Clavicle Necklace Female Jewelry.

Four necklaces arrived, all silver-so far, so good. Two of them are on silver cord, not chains. That's fine, I guess, but the cord looks cheap. The left-most necklace in my picture above, has a tassel on the bottom made of several small chains. As soon as I put it on, a chain fell down my shirt. I wore it to work and when I got into my car later that day to go home, I found two more of the small chains on the floor of my car.

I absolutely love the one that has a silver knot shape with the tassels hanging down. That one seems to have stayed intact, though I've worn it many times so far.

The one with the three flat circles is just okay. It's nice to wear for day to day use, but it's not going to knock anyone's socks off.

I love silver jewelry, but I don't like spending a lot of money all the time, so these do make for good day to day wear. Other than the one that seems to be losing chains by the second, the rest are of decent quality.

Since I'm not sure what the pricing is on these right now, I cannot tell you if they're a good value or not. I can only share with you my experience, which I have done.

title: NO
text:
When I requested this from Vine, I was super excited! At the $40.00 price point, I knew I wasn't exactly getting the best of the best, but it does look nice in the picture. The reality is different.

First, the necklace is so darn small, I felt like I was choking. I couldn't put it on myself, due to how tight it was and also due to arthritis in my fingers. When my husband got it on me it was not comfortable to wear.

The chain doesn't really look like the one pictured. To be honest, it looks super cheap. The stone itself is really, really pretty and that's the only good thing I have to say about this necklace.

If I had a spare silver chain I would take the stone off this and hang it from that instead, but I don't. I think for this price, you could do just as well if not WAYYYY better at the Walmart jewelry counter.

title: Pretty, But Has Some Issues
text:
I liked this necklace when I saw it in the picture, but in person, not so much.

First, the chains that are hanging down are what first attracted me. However, with my necklace the chains are unevenly placed which makes it look kind of funny.

Second, the cord that the beads and chains hang from is a bright blue and...almost yarn like and the yarns snags easily. If you look closely at the pictures on the left, specifically the last one, (up top, next to the item), you can see a snag in it.

Lastly, if you accidentally drop it while trying to put it on, good luck, because everything slides off the necklace and all over the floor. There's no knot or anything to prevent that from happening. (However, this makes it easy for me to rearrange the chains that hang down, so that they look more even.)

Overall, it's okay and I'll probably wear it, if I can get it on without dropping it.

title: Pretty Design
text:
These earrings are cool looking, and because of the material, (plastic?), they are very lightweight and don't pull your ears down and that's always a plus.

So far, I've only worn them twice and have received compliments both times. I'm not sure about the durability though, since they seem kind of flimsy? I haven't had any problems so far, and if I do, I will come back and update this review. For now, I like these a lot!

title: Comfy!!
text: My daughter loves these leggings, Very good quality. My kid loves them Comfortable and nice.

title: Very cute set! Great gifts for teen couples.!!
text: Very cute set! Great gifts for teen couples. I love them so much! The necklaces and bracelets are so cute!!! My partner loves his! I would highly suggest getting them. The necklaces are designed really well !!

title: Great sunglasses!!!
text: I was looking for a replacement pair after I broke my favorite pair of sunglasses that were similar in style to these. These are great and definitely worth the price. I don't like paying much for sunglasses because I lose or break them easily. The only thing I don't like about these is the nose piece gets caught in my hair when I place them on top of my head. My old glasses had that built in to the frame. I also wish the metal was silver rather than gold. But overall, these are a great buy!

title: Good One!
text: They’re definitely one of the better quality sunglasses out there for a fraction of the price,  but don’t be fooled by its price. The build quality on these is incredible and they look and feel like they should be 2x their current price! I love these so much that I just had to order another pair after I dropped and scratched mine (totally my fault). I hope they add more variants to their collection!

title: My favorite chain.
text: I really like this necklace. It’s shiny and looks well built.This chain is fabulous. It looks very much like "the real thing," and so i use it for everyday casual wear. It's a very sturdy chain..specially this chain looks like 3 different kind of chains with one set..

title: Nice designs and verities of rings
text:
Ring verities are awesome and looks good with all kind of sizes. But they are for short time and find them very comfortable wear.
I don't think this rings golded coating will stay longer. With in hours those rings color changed.

title: Comfortable Fitting Sports Bra
text:
My wife loves it when she gets to put on a well fitting item of clothing such as a sports bra or new pair of sneakers. This was certainly the case with the YEEPSYS Sports Bra for Women, Criss-Cross Back Padded Strappy Sports Bra.

She says, “It feels so comfortable that It seems like the item was made just for me. After I put this sports bra, I was amazed at the comfortable feel and perfect fit. It was so great! I felt satisfaction with this item and highly recommend it.”

title: Heavy Jogging Pants Best for Fall or Winter Exercising
text: We made the mistake of ordering the Amazon Brand - Goodthreads Women's Heritage Fleece Basic Jogger Pant during the late spring. They are heavy and think and definitely geared to fall and winter outdoor exercising. But for those seasons, they are nearly perfect. In fact, my wife’s only concern is that they tend to be sized too large.

title: Small, but Comfortable Walking Socks
text: When I first opened the package and looked at the WXXM Men's Athletic Breathable Mo Show Socks, I thought that they barely looked like socks at all. They were so small looking. When I put them on they barely cleared my heal. But when I went out for my daily walk I realized that these are very comfortable walking socks. Yes, they may look like “more show” socks, but they are good for exercising. They kept my feet dry as I walked.

title: Cute, Well Made Pin - Looks a Bit Like LEGOs
text: The AN KINGPiiN Men's Yellow Smiley Pill Lapel Pin Is very cute. To me the smiley face looks like it was made with miniature LEGOs. (Since I am a fan of LEGO kits, this strikes a nice chord for me.) The pin appears to be well made and has no trouble staying in place. It adds some flare to a jacket or shirt.

title: Classy and Elegant Earrings
text: My wife tells me that she really likes the Umamebet Elegant Leaf Dangle Earrings for Women Gold Plated Crystal Teardrop Earrings. She finds them to be classy and elegant. They are just the right size—not overly large and not too small. She feels that they are dressy and would go well for a formal or semi-formal occasion or even for dinner out with your husband (ahem!)

title: Stylish and Well Made Jacket
text: The Charis Allure Women's Casual Work Office Open Front Blazer Jacket is stylish and well made. The jacket works equally well with a dress, skirts or even jeans. My wife finds this to be one of her favorite jackets.

title: Five Star Hat
text:
I asked my wife what she thought of the Orchid Row Women’s Floppy Hat. Without hesitation she said, “It’s great! I love the hat. It has green leaves and a cute pink flower. It’s very fashionable. Let’s give it a five star review.”

There is nothing else that I can add to her review.

title: Warm, Good Looking Scarf and Beanie
text:
My wife finds the Orchid Row Women's LOVE ME Block Letter Knit Beanie and Scarf to be warm, good looking and comfortable. She loves the fact that it says “LOVE ME” on both the scarf and the beanie. The scarf and beanie that we were sent is blue and gold—exactly matching the colors of our favorite sport teams.

This is a classy and functional scarf and beanie. One that will no doubt get much use this winter.

title: Nice Looking, Well Made Hat
text: The Orchid Row Women's Fashion Wranger Hat with Velvet Band looks great on my wife’s head. The blue and black color is very sophisticated and will match with most coats. The hat uses quality, durable material. It is suitable to wear out for most occasions.

title: Well Fitting, Comfortable Cap that Has an Adjustable Back Strap with Fastener
text:
Everybody who wears denim jeans and shirts needs a denim cap because they look so cool together. However, the Rebel Canyon Men's Denim Unstructured Dad Hat has more than just style going for it.

The cap is very light weight and almost feels like it's not even there when you wear it. The cap is very comfortable and it is adjustable to fit most sized heads. I especially like that, instead of using a Velcro fastener, Rebel Canyon selected an adjustable back strap with a metal fastener to adjust the size of the cap. It's more retro and that fits with the cap's style. While the Velcro is easier to use especially if several people wear the same cap, I find that the back strap with fastener to be a more reliable manner to adjust the cap size.

While wearing the cap is a walking advertisement for Rebel Canyon, who wouldn't find the idea of walking around with the word "Rebel" marked on their forehead to be something of a statement!

title: Feminine, Lovely and Versatile Scarf
text: The Orchid Row's Lace Trim Lightweight Travel Scarf is lovely, very feminine and versatile. The lace adds a nice dressy touch to the scarf. It will add class to any ensemble. The material feels good and, with proper care, it should last for some time.

title: Good Looking Top that Works Equally Well with Shorts or Jeans
text: The Serene Bohemian Women's Round Neck Viscose Top is a winner. My wife says that it fits well and I say that it looks great. The fact that it happens to be my wife's favorite color (yellow) is a plus. It is gorgeous, fashionable and versatile top that goes equally well with jeans or shorts. It is current and stylish.

title: Nice women's scarf.
text:
This scarf goes with anything!
The fabric is soft and doesn't irritate the skin.
There were no flaws in the fabric upon receiving, and this scarf has held up nicely.

title: Very pretty Formal dress.
text:
This dress is very pretty.
The dress hugs my body the right way, and fits as expected.
Fabrics of the dress are soft against the skin.
The flowers are a little out of focus I would say.

title: Run small
text:
These pants run a little small.
I got size 10 for my 7 year old who wears size 10 in everything, and they were too short.
The material feels almost like a nylon to me.
I ended up donating these.

title: Great fit, very warm!
text: My son wears a size two and we got size 2/3 and they fit perfect! He says these are his favorite slippers ever! These slippers have a memory foam bottom inside for extra comfort for your little ones! These are all around great kid's slippers!

title: Great plus size stockings
text: This two pack is a great value! I'm not sure why the model's whole body is inside them HAHA, but they are really great. These tights fit exactly as expected with a little extra room, just how every girl loves her tights! These tights go with all my skirts and dresses I own. I have worn and washed these tights several times and have not experienced any runs or rips. Five stars!

title: Cute on!
text: Ok- honestly I got these and thought- nope! I just didn’t like them that much looking at them in the box. They say there for a month or so. Then I happened to wear a shirt that matched the look really well. I put them on and loved them. I ended up getting several compliments on them! I have long thick hair and I need a larger earring. These are big without being heavy. Way cuter on!

title: Worn a lot
text: I really like this. It’s boho in a good way. I like that it has an adjustable slip knot. It falls nicely on my neck and it’s not scratchy which I was worried about. Nice necklace!

title: Pretty costume jewelry
text: These are pretty jewelry and very lightweight. The circle ones are pretty easy to put in , but the others have a bend on the end that is pretty pointy and makes it hard to just slide them right in your ears on the go. Standing in front of a mirror doing it is fine.

title: Cute and jingly
text: These are cute to add as an accessory. They are not too big and fit nicely. They are mostly gold, but there are a few spots that have not enough gold coloring. (Really not noticeable). I wore them with one of my boho wraps and they went nicely.

title: Bigger than picture
text:
They were bigger then the picture. I was actually surprised when I opened the box. I thought they were more silver and it was more pearl type look. I know it says pearl hoops bit to me it looked like silver balls.
They do look a little cheap to be honest. Not sure if I will have anything to wear them with. Pearls se traditional, yet they are so big... a strange combo.

title: Delicate and pretty
text: This ring is very pretty and sparkly. It would be a nice addition to another ring as an extra band or pretty on its own. I can see this as a starter piece of jewelry for a child as it’s tiny. It looks very authentic- not cheap. Very pretty.

title: Nice minimalist wallet
text: I typically use a large bifold wallet but when I travel I tend to go lighter. I just want my 2 ID's, a credit card and some cash and for that there is no reason to have my large wallet. Not knowing what adventure I have coming next the thought of having the bulky wallet with no secure place to put it isn't appealing to me. This wallet is very well built and does everything I need it to plus the added RFID blocking is a huge bonus. The minimalist life isn't for everyone, me included but there is a time and place for everything.

title: A little heavy but very pretty
text: These are very pretty and can be worn on any occasion. They appear to be well made and should last a while. The gold plating was well done and didn't cause any skin reactions that are typical with cheaper jewelry. A nice addition to the costume jewelry box

title: Heavy duty
text: This key chain is heavy for its size. Great quality key ring is included and the engraving is deep in the metal so it wont wear off anytime soon. Great reminder to anyone who gets down or is pushed around. After a hard day at work seeing this on your way out of there is a wonderful way to add a smile to the day

title: Good size, lightweight but heavy duty
text: This backpack seems to be just the perfect size for my daughter to carry supplies needed for beauty school. She was using a duffel bag to carry 2 practice heads and all her supplies but the single strap was hurting her. This backpack easily replaced her heavy canvas duffel bag with room to spare. She can now easily get all her supplies from the house along with the baby and diaper bag and is very happy. The reflective strips give me another since of security knowing that while shes walking across the parking lot in the dark there is an extra added chance of her being seen.

title: Very cute scarf!
text: This "Orchid Row's Classic Jersey Loop Scarf IVORY O/SOrchid Row's Classic Jersey Loop Scarf IVORY O/S" is a very cute scarf! I love how cute it is and how comfortable the fit is. Definitely recommend this!

title: Overtime they tarnish
text:
I needed some new earrings, so I got the "14K Gold Plated Black Acrylic Three Circle Stud Earrings Fashion Earrings with S925 Silver needle for Women Girl Gifts Valentines/Birthday/ Anniversary / Mother’s Day14K Gold Plated Black Acrylic Three Circle Stud Earrings Fashion Earrings with S925 Silver needle for Women Girl Gifts Valentines/Birthday/ Anniversary / Mother’s Day" as I like things that hang down.
After some use in the last 6 months, I can say they have started to tarnish. The gold platting is wearing and it isn't hold it's shine. For the price, it is okay, however I wouldn't recommend it.

title: Lasted all summer long!
text:
My daughters got the CASSIECA 16Pcs Beach Anklet Bracelets for Women Set Vsco Bracelets Adjustable Waterproof Handmade Braided Rope Bracelet Boho Sunflower String Bracelets Friendship Anklets for Women Teen GirlsCASSIECA 16Pcs Beach Anklet Bracelets for Women Set Vsco Bracelets Adjustable Waterproof Handmade Braided Rope Bracelet Boho Sunflower String Bracelets Friendship Anklets for Women Teen Girls for summer use. Now that it has been a few months I can tell you this, it is a great set. Some are slightly larger than others, so they even included me in their summer anklet fun.
I would wear it in the shower and in the pool without concern. Overall they were an amazing value and I highly recommend.

title: Great gift!
text: This "Lcherry Good Luck Elephant Charm Bracelet Evil Eye Handmade Red Cord Ajustable Bracelet Friendship Gifts for Women" works very well as a gift! I got this as a gift for a friend and she loves it. She is a huge fan of elephants, so this fits her very well. Highly recommend.

title: Really shields against the sun.
text: These have nice large lens.  They are definitely polarized.  I wore these out on our boat to help see with the reflection off the water.  It greatly reduced the glare.  These are a little masculine looking to me.  But I guess they are more unisex.  I didn't find them to be very feminine.  They are comfortable and reduce glare.  Exactly what I needed.

title: Runs true to size.
text: I got these shorts in a size L.  Sometimes I get XL.  But these were perfect in size L.  I have a 38" waist and 42" hips.  I am 5/8" tall and they come down to about 5" above my knees.  They have lots of stretch.  They are high waisted.  The top panel is not a large elastic waistband.  It's a stretchy piece with a thin elastic at the top.  They do stay up quite well and don't roll.  And they have pockets!  My large iPhone fits easily.  They are super soft and very comfortable.  Not too hot.  I just wash them and throw them in the dryer.  Done!

title: Slouchy type boots.
text: These slippers are so soft!  The outsides are a soft woven looking texture.  The insides are thick fleece.  If your feet get cold regularly, these are for you!  They are super warm.  The bottoms have a textured rubber sole to keep from sliding on slick floors.  The outsides are a peachy colored pink and the insides are white.  They are not as pink as they appear in the picture.  These can be washed in the washing machine.  I just sit them out to dry.  They are made in China.

title: Run true to size.
text: I wear a size 9 shoe.  I got these in size 9 and they fit perfectly.  My foot measures 10".  The heels are low and helps hold your foot in when you walk.  It does tend to flop a little when I walk.  But it is because it's a slip on.  You just slip your foot in easily without any effort.  The plaid is a flannel type print.  The main body of the shoe is solid black in similar fabric.  The inside is super soft!  It's padded fleece on the insole.  The sole is a textured rubber for non-slip.  They are cute and warm.

title: Dainty.
text: I got this for my 9 year old granddaughter.  It's dainty enough for her.  It's simple but elegant looking.  She thinks she's wearing real diamonds!  The heart isn't too big and gaudy.  The chain is thin and lightweight.  It makes a nice gift.  Comes in a small gift box.

title: Not yoga pants.
text: These are definitely not yoga pants.  They are leggings.  They are not capri length but just a little longer.  They are not high waisted!  They are hard to pull on.  I was constantly pulling them up.  The fabric is kind of thick.  I love the pockets though.  My big Iphone fits in them and doesn't fall out.  The sizing is off.  They just aren't very comfortable.

title: Long, thick socks.
text: These can be worn by men and women.  I am a woman. They aren't too terribly tight.  On men I would think they would be tighter.  They come all the way up to my knees.  I am 5'8" tall and wear a size 9 shoe.  I like to wear compression socks when taking long trips in the car or on a plane.  These are nice and thick.  They will be great for winter.  A tad too hot for summer unless you are in air conditioning all the time.  My feet tend to get cold before the rest of me does.  So, these do help.  These socks have some funky designs!  There's a black with yellow and red flames going up the sides.  There's a royal blue with aqua diagonal stripes.  There's a black with red, white and blue zig zag stripes.  But my favorite is the patriotic pair.  They are navy blue with red and white stripes, lighter blue background with white stars and a navy blue Statue of Liberty on the other side.  They are super cute.  I wish I could figure out how to wear them with something so they will show.  None of these will show when I wear them unfortunately.  There's one pair that is a size large and the the others are L/XL.  There is a slight difference in the two.  But not really that noticeable.

title: Stunning!
text: The colors in this bracelet are so pretty.  You can wear it with almost anything.  It can make an outfit dressy.  Or you can wear it with jeans for a boho look.  I have to agree with others about it snagging.  I didn't want to take off a star for that because it's pretty much inevitable in this type bracelet.  The ends can be bent back more and coated with a drop of glue to get rid of the points.  This pretty much fits any size wrist.  I have small wrists and it fits me just fine.  It will open up bigger for larger wrists.  Comes in a small burlap bag.  Would make a great gift.

title: Elegant looking.
text: This is a set of (5) bangle bracelets.  I got the brass finish.  One is a hammered look, two have small cutouts, and two are diagonal striped.  They can be worn stacked for a boho gypsy look or singularly.  They appear to be well made and I don't expect them to tarnish.  Comes in a small canvas bag for gift giving.

title: Very flattering!
text: I usually wear an XL in sweatshirts.  I got this in a L and it fits great.  So, I would say it runs a little big.  It is a more fitted look than what I normally wear in sweatshirts.  And it's VERY flattering!  I know.  A flattering sweatshirt?  But it is.  The arm holes are a little offset off the shoulders.  That makes it very comfortable and non-restricting.  The chevron stripe goes down the sleeve which makes it more flattering.  Now about the quality of the fleece.  It's thick and very soft.  The front hand pocket is warm and doesn't add a lot of bulk.  The hood is plenty big and draws closed with large, wide ties!  The sleeves are the perfect length for me.  I am 5'8" tall and this comes down to middle of my hips.  It measures 22" from shoulder to bottom of the band. It says it's 60% cotton and 40% polyester.  It also says it can be washed and dried in the machine.  I always hang my sweatshirts to dry so that they do not become too short.  This seems like a quality sweatshirt.  It's made in China.

title: Is indeed packable.
text: Some hats say they are packable but end up not living up to that claim.  This one is truly packable.  Folds and smashes flat.  The feel of the fabric is kind of like a micro fiber - smooth and soft.  The brim is large enough to thoroughly cover your face and the back of your neck.  You can tighten the band to make it more secure on your head.  There's a tie bow in the back which is cute and functional.  It helps tighten up the hat on your head.  I like to wear hats with ties when out on the boat so they don't blow off.  This one stays on very well as it sits down so far on my head.  I really like the look and the color is nice as well.  It comes with it's own little carry case.  I will get a lot of wear out of this one!

title: Cute!
text: I got these for my 13 year old granddaughter.  Oh my gosh!  She was so excited.  She started naming off all her friends she could give them to!  The young girls love these things.  I am so glad the strings are adjustable.  I have tried to tie these things on her wrists before!  What a pain.  So it's great that the little knots make these adjustable.  The colors are bright an fun.  The charms are all different.  The only problems she has is deciding who got which one.  The metal does tarnish a little if they're worn for an extended time.  But the girls don't mind!  Such a cute idea.  She will probably be wanting to order some more.

title: Long kimono.
text: This kimono is longer than most I have.  It comes down to about 3-4 inches above my ankles.  My husband thought I was wearing a coat!  It's very sheer.  So, there's not way it gives the warmth of a coat.  It's a black background with assorted colorful flowers.  The sleeves are 3/4 length.  It's made to be worn open in the front.  There are no closures.  I wear it over jeans with a tank top.  I do not like to wear sleeveless tops because of the way my arms look.  This is a nice look without extra warmth.

title: Low cut.
text: These are low cut but not as much no show.  In athletic shoes these will not show.  I have some low cut walking shoes and these do show.  They go up my ankles some.  They have an elastic band all around the ankle opening.  There's the rubberized patch in the inside of the heel to keep it from slipping down into your shoe.  These are a little thicker cotton sock.  The tops are mesh. They do keep my feet dry.  There's a seam over the toe but it doesn't bother me.  These are very colorful!  They are kind of a patchwork design.  The main colors are light blue, navy, black, grey, green, red, white and purple.  I like different colorful socks!  These fit the bill!  I wash these in the washing machine but lay them out to dry.  They do shrink.  They are 80% cotton, 15% acrylic and 5% spandex.  Made in China.

title: They don't show!
text: I like wearing these socks in my walking shoes.  They are not high cut athletic shows.  It's hard to find socks that don't show for these lower cut shoes.  These are a little heavier than some.  They are mesh which keep my feet cooler. They have seams over the toe. The heel has a rubberized spot on the inside to hold them in place.  There's also a band of elastic around the top of the heel.  They stay put!  I hate when my socks slide down into my shoes.  These do not!  These come with tan, black, white, and grey.  Two pairs in each color.  They are 80% cotton and 15% acrylic and 5% spandex.  I wash mine in the washing machine.  I lay them out to dry because they do shrink if you put them in the dryer.  They dry very quickly.

title: Super nice goggles!
text: First off these come in a nice hard plastic carrying case.  It's a great to protect them.  They are blue around the edges.  The strap is adjustable to fit from a teen to an adult.  Love that they are anti-fog!  Comfortable and quality made.

title: Big and fluffy!
text: These ear muffs are so fun!  They're big and they are super fluffy.  The colors are purple, blue, black, gray and a tad of yellow.  They are on a black felt headband.  Puffs measure 5" wide and 3" thick.  Not only do they keep your ears warm but you can still hear with them on!  Nice!!

title: Great jacket
text: So even though this is a mens jacket, it looked cute so I got it for myself. The blue color is super cute, it’s like a teal color. The inside is lined with fur so it’s really warm. It’s very thick and it’s also waterproof, so it’s great for skiing. We went skiing in Whistler for Christmas and it was perfect. All I needed under it was a tshirt and a thin thermal. It’s really well made and I love that the hood is removable. Overall, great jacket at a very good price.

title: Looks great
text: The design and thought process behind this case is solid. The leather really makes the case stand out and I have received multiple compliments about it. The air pods fit perfectly inside as well. The only downside is that the plastic interior of the case does not flex enough to allow the lid to open fully so it kind of pops in and out. It still works well and this may be the design of the case, but it may need to be separated into two pieces to achieve full open. I am still very happy with the case though!

title: Great value
text: Great sunglasses for the price. The lenses are big and clear and I love the polarization. I wear these while I’m driving and when I go fishing and they work perfect for my needs. Easy to clean and easy to store. Great product!

title: Nice sunglasses!
text: Opening the box, these sunglasses are presented very well. They are packaged like rather expensive sunglasses. The build quality seems nice with nice material choices. So far they seem sturdy and I really like that they are polarized. They have not scratched easy and they are easy to clean. Great product!

title: Nice belt!
text: I am pretty impressed by this belt. It is nice thick leather and it seems to be good quality. The band is a little wide as well as the buckle but I like it. The stitching has held up well so far. I will update the review if anything changes. Great belt!

text: Comfortable t-shirt, nice materials, perfect for lounging, do errands,casual pair with shorts or jeans.

title: Very lightweight shorts with reflective stripes for jogging
text:
Full elastic waist jogging shorts made of 93% Polyester and 7% spandex.

Super lightweight, very comfortable. Perfect for jogging because they have a reflective stripes on the side.

What’s really unique about these shorts is the zippered pocket on the back.

Perfect shorts for jogging and working out.

title: Very lovely set of earrings, perfect set to match my emerald necklace
text:
Beautiful!

I was given a beautiful white gold necklace with my first grandson’s birthstone, an emerald. These earrings complement the necklace nicely. Perfect set to wear to an upcoming wedding.

These earring have prints with a nice hinged cover. They are cubic zirconias and add so much sparkle. But, I’m really having trouble wearing them. I can’t seem to get them to fit my pierced hole. The stud is really thick. I’ve compared them to my other earrings and they are about twice the thickness.

title: Nice looking beaded bracelet, careful with the ends, can catch on clothing
text:
Very colorful, beaded cuff bracelet.

Reminds me of the 60’s and 70’s. Very colorful beads braided into a cuff style bracelet. It comes packaged in a burlap drawstring bag. Perfect for gift giving.

One thing that will prevent me from wearing the bracelet is the ends of the beaded link have rough wires. They catch on everything. Clothing, blankets, towels; even the burlap bag it is stored in. It even pulled some of the threads in the bag.

If you really like the bracelet and want to wear, I recommend that you tighten the ends.

title: Super comfortable socks, great for long hike and short strolls
text:
Great hiking socks are essentials when you trek on long hikes. These socks are a Poly/Cotton with just enough nylon and Elastane to give them the stretch they need. They wash and dry perfectly and are ready for another adventurous day.

They come in all sizes for men and women. My favorite feature is they are super lightweight and absorb sweat away from my feet.
There’s also added cushion in the underfoot, toe, and heel; really helps keep my feet comfortable.

My favorite feature is there are no seams around my toes. This is a pet peeve of mine, I hate strings around my toes. Therefore, these will not cause any blisters or discomfort during the hike.

They also have great arch support helping my feet feel like they are getting a massage as I hike. They are perfect for all kinds of hiking. Perfect for my camping trips and my hikes with my daughter in tow.

title: Such a cute little sweater with a sweet bunny, perfect for Spring
text:
Very stylish knitted sweater with a sweet little bunny on the front. Perfect style with a round neck and short sleeves.

Comfy and casual. Perfect for skirts or pants. Really nice for those cooler days and great for Spring.

Made of 100% Cotton and best to hand wash and dry flat.

title: Very pretty petite cowrie shell bracelet
text:
Beautiful, simple, cowrie shell bracelet made with an intricately braided wax cord. Natural cowrie shells are attached to the cord throughout the bracelet. Very soft pink colored enameled shells.

The bracelet length is adjustable from 6.7” to 13.4”. All you need to do is adjust the slip knot to adjust the length.

It is recommended to clean by hand with a soft cloth. Best to store in flannel to avoid damage. Be sure to keep it dry.

The package includes:
(1) 1 shell bracelet
(2) 1 pink velvet drawstring

100% Money Back Guarantee

title: Unique length, moisture wicking socks
text:
These socks come beautifully packaged in a lovely gift box and each sock is individually wrapped. They are very soft, moisture wicking material.

But, the length is a little odd. They are not ankle socks and they are not crew socks either. They are positioned in between!

They are made of cotton and feels very soft. They keep your feet dry, cool, and comfy. Machine washable and dry quickly.

Great pair of socks if you are okay with the unusual length.

Summary:
(1) 97% Combed cotton/ 3% Spandex
(2) Chitosan is blended in the yarn to provide anti odor effect
(3) Relieves athletes foot
(4) helps to get rid of embarrassing smelly feet
(5) “Y" shaped deep heel pocket ensures sock fits the contours of the foot
(6) seamless/reinforced heel and toe
(7) breathable and lightweight
(8) keep your feet ventilated and comfortable

title: Odd style, very lightweight knit, better suited as casual dress
text:
Very unique style and flimsy, knit material, better suited for dress down or even a bathing suit cover up. I was so confused, from the pictures, I thought it looked like a dressy dress.

I actually ordered it to wear to a funeral. Even with a slip, this is not appropriate. It’s made of of such a thin fabric, it’s better suited for summer wear.its a pull-on over your head style. It does have a gathered section on one side; this is where it’s a little odd. This scrunched design in the side is not very flattering. It leaves the rest of the dress just hanging.

It is machine washable, recommend to use cold water, no bleach and do NOT use clothes dryer. Best to hang dry. With this in mind, it’s a pretty decent material to travel with. No wrinkles.

Summary:
* 95%Viscose 5% Elastane
* Pull on closure
* Crew neck, short sleeve, solid loose fit long dress
* Machine Washable, cold water; Do not bleach, cold iron and hang dry

title: Cute, adorable hats that have 50+ UPF protection
text:
Set of two of the cutest hats ever. It includes a baseball hat and a bucket hat, both are made of 100% Cotton and Washable! The bucket hat is a soft blue color with the cutest ruffle trim. It is sculpted in 6 panels with a curved peak.

The baseball cap is actually made of white eyelet and is so adorable. So cute and perfect hats to protect your little one’s face and head due to the hats rated at UPF 50+.

Fits our 16 month old granddaughter. She loves hats! So glad because these hats protect her fair skin from the sun. She’s our outdoor queen, she’s outside almost all day! I’m so glad we found some really cute hats that will keep her safe.

Summary:
(1) 100% Cotton
(2) Broderie Cap and Chambray bucket hat
(3) Soft Foldable / Packable
(4) Machine Wash on Gentle Cycle
(5) Caps are perfect sized for ages 6-18M
(6) Adjustable elastic band at the back
(7) Bucket Hat Cinch Chin strap

title: Great umbrella, perfect for rainy days and sunny days, too
text:
Umbrellas are not just for rainy days! I am very sensitive to the sun and need to stay in the shade. This umbrella is perfect for my needs because it is easy to hold but can also stand up to windy days.

Because of the 10 ribs, it is a little heavier than other umbrellas.

Very stylish with automatic open and close function. Just press the button and it pops open! Then just pop the button again and it closes!

title: Super comfy, super cute!
text:
Unisex Animal Pattern Breathable Novelty Printed Crew socks. Created for ladies who love their pets! Very comfy, cute socks!

They are very stylish, made of polyester and elastane. Easy to wash and wear! They are lightweight, versatile and sweat wicking! Very comfortable for all-day wear. One size fits all.

One size fits all? Yep, my little one figured that out and now she thinks they are her socks! (She’s only 15 months old and they go all the way up to her thigh!) our little fashionista!

title: Great comfortable, no slide, moisture wicking, no-show socks
text:
Panvbo 8 Pairs Womens No Show Socks Casual Low Cut Invisible Loafer Liner Cotton Socks

Perfect shape and fit for my new slip ons. These no show socks are the perfect solution for my theme park walking days.

They have a low-cut invisible design, makes these casual socks fit my shoes perfectly! Oh, yeah, they’re comfortable, too.

Summary:
(1) high quality cotton
(2) mesh knit at top makes them breathable and comfortable
(3) lightweight and sweat-wicking
(4) moisture wicking
(5) will not slide off
(6) new silicone rubber design prevents slipping

Package includes 8 pairs of no show socks

RISK FREE GUARANTEE

title: Great lightweight hat, practical and good looking!
text:
Soft felt hat, two tone, very sporty looking. Not a true “cowboy” hat, but similar style.

There’s just enough of a rim to keep the sun off of your neck.

It’s very lightweight, just the perfect size.

title: Fur Earmuffs!  Yes!  Now I'm sporting even in the cold weather!
text:
Great looking ear muffs of faux fur. Made of soft browns and very warm. Fits on your head easily and folds for storage.

Looks great! Feels great! What else do you need? Pair it up with a faux fur scarf and you can then head to town!

title: Yep!  It's a fur scarf! Now aren't you something!
text:
Very nice looking fur scarf that will definitely keep you warm A very soft blend of browns and just the right length.

Add it to any jacket and it really dresses up the look. So, here you are with a fux fur scarf that looks great and is practical, too!

title: Cute watch
text: My daughter has started a bit of a watch collection, and she loves this one! It is unique and honestly a great size and fit. The only negative that she has noticed is that the second band that holds the watch band in place is rather itchy against her skin. It is held together with a single stich that bothers her a little. Other than that, this is a great watch.

title: Cute, but don't work well
text: My daughter was so excited to get these earrings, they are very beautiful and came in a nice box. However... In order to get them to stay put you basically have to bend them to the size needed. They also fell off within a few minutes of wearing them. Not worth the price!

title: Decent
text:
Nice, classic aviators. Look great on me and my son. Love the deep, mirror blue color.

Quality is medium. I'm worried about these getting damaged. They just don't seem to be holding up to general use - let along typical abuse if you're the type (like me) that leaves them lying around.

Very light, very comfortable.

Lenses are hard to keep clean - they're fingerprint and oil magnets!

All that said, I definitely recommend these. Size and balance is very nice.

title: Huge
text:
okay, I have to start out by saying that the quality of these glasses is just fine. I would not put it on par with stuff costing 10 times as much, but I certainly would say it is every bit as good as any other sunglasses I have used or held at $25 or under.

I am giving it a B grade because I think they are just huge. I no they are being sold as oversized, so I guess you better take that serious. I have a big head, and these from my perspective are just over the top. I guess there are those who like huge glasses, but I just don't see too many guys typically doing that, and I guess these have more of a masculine frame characteristic and so there you go.

As I already mentioned, the quality is decent and the fit and finish is very good. I saw no issue whatsoever with the frame, hinges and so forth. The fake leather caze is actually pretty nice with a metal flex enclosure at the end.

title: decent polarized shades
text: these come in a nice bamboo tube. Lens shade is a typical dark gray, the blue color is just the mirror coating. However, the blue coated lenses are a little more color neutral than the orange ones I also got. The orange coated ones have a bit of a green color hue. The arms are spring loaded to prevent breakage if they get extended too far. An advantage of the spring is it also helps keep them snug to your head without being to tight and adjust for different head sizes, even my little head

title: Work great
text:
These work great. The scoop area holds itself open perfectly and catches everything that falls, crumbs, spit out drinks and spoonfulls of food. I've tried other brands that constantly collapse closed on themselves and those are worthless. These aren't those.

The color of these are very nice and there is a good variety of sizing options available. (Although I would say you need at least 2 of the buttons secured in order to hold it on well.)

Overall I recommend these.

title: Super comfy and POCKETS
text: I really love these, the tummy comes up at the perfect height and are very comfortable. The pockets are gold as I wear this style bottoms every day while I'm not working out. But I am chasing 2 young kids around and the pockets are amazing for holding my keys and phone during such chases. These have been holding up well to a lot of wear and washes.

title: Super thin material, very thick buttons and label says "Ripe and Raw" on it
text:
The fabric of this dress is super thin and kind of scratchy. It also has super thick buttons on the back that are very uncomfortable when leaned back on while wearing.

On top of this being unflattering and uncomfortable to wear, the label on the back neck says "Ripe and Raw". I is printed onto the fabric and is not a tag that can be cut out. I do not feel like this is appropriate for little girls' clothing and I want to make sure to point it out in case a potential buyer was not aware of the brand and label. Personally I don't feel comfortable with my young kids wearing clothing that says Ripe and Raw on it.

title: Love This Dress!
text: I bought this dress in green for a wedding. It's very comfortable with some stretch to it (which was very helpful for breastfeeding). I received lots of compliments on it. I also wore it for a date night. Despite its thicker material, I hardly sweated in it during 85 degree weather.  The only down side to this dress: it is very low cut if you are busty. I was a little worried about falling out while dancing and bending down to pick up my children. I had to do some adjusting once in a while but nothing too bad.

title: Good selection
text: This is a nice selection of "different" jewelry. I know they're going to get scratched pretty soon and turn orange, so I'm prepared. The sizes have a lot of range. The nonadjustable ones are way too big for my fingers, but the adjustable ones fit without much adjustment needed. Three are nonadjustable.

title: Beautiful design
text:
The "deer horn" part of the name threw me off. I wasn't interested in hanging a shiny dead animal lookalike around my neck. But I reconsidered upon another's recommendation, and I'm glad I did. This is a very nice necklace. It can pass as a nice design without being too reminiscent of animal horns.

The pendant catches the light very nicely. It's neither too big or too small. It's that prefect in between size, where it's still eye catching, but doesn't takeover the entire outfit.

It can be worn for almost all occasions - adding some glitz to an everyday outfit, or even for an evening out. It's nicely versatile in that way.

title: Nice large necklaces
text: These necklaces are nice looking and large sized. They're very noticeable on an outfit, and really help to dress up any look. They look cheapish, not meant for evening wear, but look really good on an everyday/work outfit.

title: Great metallic tee
text:
This top is somewhere between dressy and casual. It's a simple t-shirt style, but in a great metallic color. It's hard to figure out where to wear it to because it's neither completely casual nor dressy enough for evening ware. I really like the color and fit though, so I hope I find the perfect event to wear it to.

The color is exactly as shown in the product image - a very very light gray.

Fits well. Looks good on. Material feels good - light for summer wear, but not a thin cheap material.

title: Looks really nice!
text:
Comfortable and soft. I can’t speak for warmth yet, as I haven’t worn it out in cold weather, but I like the way it feels and looks.

It's a nice soft silvery, lightly sparkly beanie. Definitely adds color to your outfit.

title: Perfect toiletry bag
text: This is a little bigger than I expected - for some reason I pictured it as a wristlet, but it's too big for that. It's a nice sized bag that can fit a shaver or other small cosmetic/toiletry items. Or it can make a great camera bag. It certainly has its uses. The leather feels tough and durable. Great for traveling with or just for keeping your items neatly categorized.

title: Well made, on the big side
text: These are too big for my wife's face, but she's petite. If you're a tall woman with a big head, they'll probably work for you. They are well made and the lenses do a good job of blocking the sun. They are similar to the Foster Grants you find at drug stores.

title: Colorful costume jewelry
text: I can't see a woman wearing this, but a young teen might like it. The bracelet is inexpensively made of fabric and beads. It comes in a gift bag. If you have a 13 year old daughter or niece who likes shiny, organic looking stuff, this just might work as a little gift.

title: Very brightly colored, decently made athletics socks
text: These are super bright in color, more bright than I expected from the photo. But I do like the design. The quality of the sock is decent enough. It's sewn well and the composition of the fabric is what you'd want out of an athletics sock. They are sized correctly. This is a novelty sock, but it isn't cheaply made at all. If you want something that will make people notice you while you're working out or playing b-ball, this pair will do the trick.

title: Decent leather, but not a practical design for coins
text: The quality of the leather is decent and thick. But this really isn't a good coin purse because it doesn't open up easily. You have to poke your fingers in the pouch to get coins out or flip the holder upside down and shake. Standard coin purses have accordion style openings for a reason. This design ignores that reason and the result is something that is best as a credit card or business card holder. It does make for a decent business card holder. You can put about 7 or 8 cards in the pouch and it does protect them well.

title: great size, non-leather is kinder to animals
text: This is a great size for your phone, reading glasses (if, like me, you are of a certain age), pack of tissues, wallet, etc. The color is neutral and so is the style (aside from the tassels). It seems sturdily built and the zipper works well. I held off on the review to see if they'd list a price, but they have not. In a big box store it would probably be around $20. If it is ever available for sale, recommend.

title: cute, comfortable, and warm!
text: I have Reynaud's syndrome, so keeping my feet warm is a challenge. These were comfortable and provided extra warmth due to the height and thickness. There's enough padding to make them comfy without shoes; they are not so bulky as to require a lot of extra room in your boots. I wore these to walk the dog and my toes didn't turn white (also, they aren't too tight in the toes, which can be another challenge). They seem to be well made and I expect them to last a while. The design is suitably trendy. Recommend!

title: Basic ties; kind of flashy
text: We were surprised by the sparkles. If you are looking for a fun, flashy, bright tie, this might be the pair for you. If you are an older person working in a conservative setting (or you need a tie for a somber occasion like a funeral), maybe not. I can't comment on the price because there isn't one listed. The quality seems like something you'd get in a TJMaxx kind of store---but there you would have the advantage of being able to see them in person.  Recommended with reservations.

title: posts are thick; ok for the price; no gift bag or box
text: I don't hate them (particularly for such a low price), nor do I love them. The quality seems ok; the pearls aren't going to detach from the posts anytime soon, and the silver is shiny. They did not irritate my skin. However, the posts are thick, which isn't a great choice for my thick ears, and after wearing them I think I prefer pearls without any visible attachment (i.e., a simpler style). If you like this style and the thick post won't be an issue for you, try them out.

title: Cute but no real sun protection
text: Note that this was designed in the UK.  What do they have there? Clouds and rain.  The holes in this hat means it's fine for keeping your hair out of your face on a windy day (and it's snug enough to stay on your head in that weather), but it's not good for sun protection. It's really cute and it does fold and pack up well.  I'm keeping it as a spare in my car for windy days, but I won't be counting on it as a sun blocker. Since that's how they are advertising it, only 3 stars.

title: Fun for teens; won't improve your cleavage
text: Despite the model, this won't improve your cleavage. With that in mind, it's really fun for teens. Looks great with a tee and shorts for beach outings or summer-themed parties.  Definitely not an expensive piece (not sure what they plan to charge), so you won't have to worry about breaking or losing it.  This would probably be $5 from a beach stall; hopefully they'll price it accordingly.

title: Not a hit with my teen
text: My teen has bushy hair like Hermione Granger in the first Harry Potter movies, and she wears headbands all the time---frequently ones she rolls from bandanas. As her mother, I'm always trying to up-level this, but the lurex foil head band has not been a hit. She says it looks too fancy for school, it's too wide for her taste, and it's a little tight.  I'm going to end up using it to keep my hair out of my face when I use a face mask.  I think it's pretty, but overall I'd call this a fail in our house.

title: The bra is missing; the straps aren't adjustable
text: It's also not particularly long. I wore it OVER a bra as one more layer for winter warmth, but I certainly wouldn't recommend it as described.

title: Cheap. Flimsy. Case smells weird.
text: If I had seen these at the corner drugstore for $9.99, I would have thought they were overpriced. This is dollar-store quality at best. They look like they would snap in a heartbeat, they aren't comfortable, and they actually rattle (like the parts weren't connected properly). They come with a case that smells weird.

title: Some question over stylishness
text:
This watch caused a lot of discussion in our family. My wife loves it. She says it has its own sort of elegance and style. I had mixed feelings. I felt the white strap clashed with the gold of the watch. The watch without the band looks great; we all agree on that.

Our (grown) daughter called the watch "tacky" but didn't have specific reasons other than she thought it looked on the cheap side. I mostly disagree and my wife completely disagrees.

Certainly you can see at once it's not a high-end watch, and it doesn't come at a high-end price. I thought it looked a little cheaper and less well manufactured than some others in the price range. But we all think it's appropriate for casual use (not elegant evenings) and would be better if the strap were changed to something color compatible.

As I like to say it, the watch is "Target" quality. It doesn't descent to the Walmart level but neither does it rise to the Neiman-Marcus range. Four stars.

title: They really do mean large
text:
No doubt that these are nice earrings. But they are not for everyone. Not at all.

My wife tried them. Now, when we ordered, we knew it said 'large' but we didn't realize it meant LARGE, maybe HUGE. These are, in a word, gigantic. When my wife put them on our daughter asked if she was going to tell our fortune. A bit of a stereotype, perhaps, but it fits.

They're nice enough in appearance, just way too big and way too loud for someone above a certain (young) age. If you're going for effect, fine. If you want to wear them as mood pieces, all well and good. But ordinary wear? Daily wear? Formal wear? Never.

We give four stars because of relatively good quality. But my wife won't be using them.

title: Useful if not especially elegant
text:
My wife uses this for times when she doesn't want to carry much more than an ID, credit cards, and cell phone. It's perfect for that, and the strap can be worn cross-body for additional security.

The purse is very lightweight and holds more than you might expect (although nothing very big, of course). We were not sure what "PU Leather" might be but it is evidently not real leather, but some sort of near-imitation. That's fine. The purse isn't really high up on the good looks and elegance scale.

That's not to say that it isn't presentable. For casual light-weight outings, it's just fine. It doesn't look in any way cheap, neither does it look anything beyond lower-middle grade. The construction quality is okay; it will last for a while if rough use is avoided.

There are some bizarre features. The purse comes with a rather large nail clipper meant to be attached to the end of the strap? I mean, really? You'd like to walk around proudly displaying your --- nail clipper?

Another oddity: the box comes with a card written in Chinese on one side and with the English words "Eyes of Love" on the other side. Very nice, but we didn't exactly see the connection. This is a utilitarian purse, not something seductive.

Overall four stars. It's a useful purse, just not exactly upscale.

title: Nice neutral colors and great for summer wear
text:
My wife likes these socks and asked me to rate them five stars. Her reasons:

1. The colors are neutral. No loud reds or anything; instead, grey, white, black. But the soft, muted colors are still quite attractive.

2. The socks are very soft and very comfortable. They are just nice to wear.

3. The socks are on the lightweight side and are more suitable for summer or warmer weather.

4. The socks seem quite well made and probably will last a while.

5. Suitable for most exercise except perhaps long distance running.

Overall good quality and value.

title: Just not to taste; very loud
text:
My wife has the following to say about this dress, which unfortunately she didn't care for.

"This dress is just not to my taste. It's too loud and it has a matronly look on me, except that's inconsistent because of the clear panel on the bottom. I think this is a dress that didn't know what it wanted to be when it grew up.

"The fit was fine. I thought the belt would be a nice touch, pulling in the middle so the dress wasn't too loose and like a mu`u mu`u, which it is without the belt, but it actually looked worse. The belt really didn't match up very well.

"Everyone has different taste and you may like this. But I didn't, and I won't be wearing it. Three stars at best."

title: Decent Rings - Seem To Open Awfully Easy - Overpriced For What You Get
text: The Milacolato 6Pcs G23 Titanium 16G Hinged Nose Rings are a decent starter set for those with nose piercings.  That being said, my daughter and my wife, who both have piercings, said that the gauges were awfully small and that the rings opened up way too easily.  So with that in mind, these rings seem to be over-priced by about $6-$8.  I wouldn't pay more than $10 for these.

title: Very Nice!
text:
The ArtGully Handcrafted Sleek & Stylish Intricately Designed Oxidized Silver Brass Choker with Adjustable Chain is very pretty and stylish. The craftsmanship is very good and unlike a set of earrings I got from ArtGully, the necklace is very sturdy and should last for quite sometime. I also liked the resealable plastic box that it was shipped in. My daughter is using it for a lot of her jewelry now!

Although the ArtGully Handcrafted Sleek & Stylish Intricately Designed Oxidized Silver Brass Choker with Adjustable Chain is not yet priced, I anticipate it being in the $15 range.

title: Decent Low Mid-Level Watch
text:
The Alloro Men's Day and Date Quartz Analog Wrist Watch is a decent men's watch for someone who is looking for a mid-level work/casual watch. Although its about 1/2" thick, it is not heavy (which tells me the quartz face is pretty thin. The packaging states that it was made in India.

The watch displays Hour/Minute/Second, the date, and the day (with Sunday in red). The windings of the watch are loose as the hour/minute hand swing very quickly when adjusted. Does not give you a sense of high quality (as several of my other watches do). The face is a nice white color so it is easy to read the time and the numbers are black roman numerals. The Date & Day are also large enough for me to read without being either TOO large or make me wish I had my reading glasses on.

The back of the watch is stainless steel so it is theoretically scratch resistant. Its also has "A Quality Watch" printed on the back which if you have to say it implies that its not. The band is some type of leather and I'm not a fan. Its thin and short (and I have narrow wrists) and the adjustable strap doesn't stay on the end of the band (its too wide) so I'm constantly fiddling with the watch. Will end up buying a new band sometime.

At this time, the Alloro Men's Day and Date Quartz Analog Wrist Watch is not priced, but because of the quality level I would assume its in the $20-25 range. If its priced higher than that, I will lower my review because it isn't worth that much. It isn't a WalMart special $15 watch, but its not a $40-$50 mid-level watch either.

title: Pretty Cool Idea
text:
The Bayinbulak Sun Hat is a pretty nice one-size-hits-all soft camo hat. I have a somewhat large head (8 3/4" on most caps), but this fit me just fine (if a bit snug). The material is nice and sturdy without being too rough or inflexible.

However, what I really liked was the mosquito netting setup that is hid inside of the top of the hat. After opening a little zipper, you just unfold the netting (which stays connected to the top of the hat) over the top of your head and pull down. It reached to the tops of my shoulders and it has a nice drawstring to keep the bottom opening snug up against the bottom of your neck. Once you don't need it anymore, it takes about 10 seconds to fold up and stow inside your hat again. Once there, I didn't feel any pressure on the top of my head. Very comfortable.

Overall, I really liked the Bayinbulak Sun Hat. By itself, it was a very nice camo work/hiking hat, but with the addition of the concealed netting that's connected to the hat so you don't lose it - VERY NICE!

title: FALSE ADVERTISING but great socks
text:
I got two different socks, the colors A10 and B5. I like both types, but love the colorful patterns of the B5. I wear a size 9-1/2 to 10 shoe, and these socks fit fine. They stay up and are warm. I work at home in slippers, and every morning I find myself reaching for these socks. I've even worn them outside in my winter boots (I usually wear thick wool socks with those boots), and while the boots were a little loose, my feet were just as warm.

I'm concerned that the seller is listing these as merino wool 53%; cotton 24%; polyester 16%; and spandex 7%. The product label says they are merino wool 35%; cotton 29%; polyester 36%. The seller needs to update its product page on Amazon. Or perhaps the manufacturer used the wrong bands around the socks. The bands say the company name of these is Fashion Boutique.

Overall, great socks at a great price.

Press the button and it extends the rod and opens the canopy. Press the button again, and it collapses the canopy making it easier to close the umbrella. The canopy is large enough for two people to huddle under. Very nicely done!

title: Very soft and works great with hooded coats
text:
UPDATE: I've upgraded this review to five stars. This is the only "scarf" I wear now in the cold weather. It keeps my head so warm and protects my face from cold winds. I love this thing!!!
---------------
It gets really cold here in Erie, Pennsylvania, so I wear a scarf whenever I go out in winter. This cowl is super soft and large. When it put it around my neck, I fold and shove the remainder inside the front of my coat, thus keeping my chest warm (I do have a fuss with the zipper, though, to keep from catching it on the cowl). When I'm walking outside, I can pull this up over my head and then put my hood over it. It acts like a hood lining that extends outside of the hood keeping my cheeks warm. It's more functional than a scarf, and it's thick so it keeps me very warm. This is my first cowl, and I'm really happy I got it.

title: No frills but functional
text: This is a relatively low frills drawstring backpack but it serves its purpose well. The main compartment is fairly roomy and with the cinched drawstring you can shape the bag how you like once you have it packed up. The outer flap has 2 clasps to keep it in place and there's 2 exterior pouch pockets that are quite on their own. Emptied out it is a very light weight bag but it is quite durable and the straps are amply padded which maintains comfort over the long haul. The material is indeed water resistant as I've used it a couple of times during slightly rainy conditions on a morning hike. The exterior also features 2 reflective stripes for added safety benefit.

It’s thin and functional, the front has a clear view pocket that’s easy to access to remove a card and the structure is much sturdier than I expected for the price. 
I've only been using it for a little over two week, so I can’t speak to it’s durability but it seems to be generally good quality and so far I like it a lot!
